ns. Basing their political conclusions on social contexts, not on abstract principles, Hume and Smith develop creative solutions to given problems.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aJustification (Theory of knowledge). 0aPolitical sciencexHistory. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook Package Archivez978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501723001zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501723001zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501723001.jpg  a978-3-11-053617-1 COR eBook Package Archive  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA